<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="const" from="2" to="10" step="2" numToSelect="4"></selectFromSequence>
  <math name="b" extend="$const[1]"/>
  <math name="d" extend="$const[2]"/>
  <math name="e" extend="$const[3]"/>
  <math name="g" extend="$const[4]"/>
  
  <selectFromSequence name="const2" from="1" to="11" step="2" numToSelect="5"></selectFromSequence>
  <math name="a" extend="$const2[1]"/>
  <math name="c" extend="$const2[2]"/>
  <math name="f" extend="$const2[3]"/>
  <math name="h" extend="$const2[4]"/>
  <math name="i" extend="$const2[5]"/>
  
  <selectFromSequence name="const3" from="1" to="9" numToSelect="8"></selectFromSequence>
  <math name="m" extend="$const3[1]"/>
  <math name="n" extend="$const3[2]"/>
  <math name="o" extend="$const3[3]"/>
  <math name="p" extend="$const3[4]"/>
  <math name="q" extend="$const3[5]"/>
  <math name="r" extend="$const3[6]"/>
  <math name="s" extend="$const3[7]"/>
  <math name="t" extend="$const3[8]"/>

  
  <math name="q1" simplify>x^2-($a+$m) x+$a*$m</math>
  <math name="q2" simplify>$b x^2 - $b*$n x - $c x + $n*$c</math>
  <math name="q3" simplify>$b x^2 - $o*$b x - $f x + $o*$f</math>
  <math name="q4" simplify>$d x^2 - $d*$p x - $a x + $a*$p</math>
  <math name="q5" simplify>$d x^2 - $d*$q x - $h x + $h*$q</math>
  <math name="q6" simplify>$e x^2 - $e*$r x - $f x + $f*$r</math>
  <math name="q7" simplify>$e x^2 - $e*$s x - $i x + $i*$s</math>
  <math name="q8" simplify>$g x^2 - $g*$t x - $h x + $h*$t</math>
</setup>


<!-- Testing

<p>$q1=(x-$a)(x-$m)</p>
<p>$q2=($b x-$c)(x-$n)</p>
<p>$q3=($b x-$f)(x-$o)</p>
<p>$q4=($d x-$a)(x-$p)</p>
<p>$q5=($d x-$h)(x-$q)</p>
<p>$q6=($e x-$f)(x-$r)</p>
<p>$q7=($e x-$i)(x-$s)</p>
<p>$q8=($g x-$h)(x-$t)</p> -->

<title>Factoring Crossword (<m>a!=1</m>)</title>

<!-- <table><title>Factoring Crossword</title> -->

<aside><title>Instructions for Crossword</title>
  <ol>
    <li>Fill the grid with factors that match the provided clues. For instance, if the clue states, "Is a factor of <math simplify>$a^2 x^2-$b^2</math>", the answer could either be <m>$a x + $b</m> or <m>$a x - $b</m>.</li>
    <li>If the answer were <m>$a x + $b</m>, you should enter <m>$a x</m> in the first box, <m>+</m> in the middle box and <m>$b</m> in the third box.</li>
    <li>Care must be taken to ensure that the filled-in factors intersect correctly both horizontally (Across) and vertically (Down). For instance, if you enter <m>$a x - $b</m> going down and <m>$c x + $d</m> going across, you've made a mistake somewhere as the signs in the middle boxes are different. They must both be positive or both be negative.
  <tabular top="minor" bottom="minor" left="minor" right="minor" width="120">
    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell><m>$a x</m></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell><m>$c x</m></cell>
      <cell><m>\pm</m></cell>
      <cell><m>$d</m></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell><m>$b</m></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>
    
    The correct solution could be <m>$a x + $b</m> and <m>$c x + $d</m>:

      <tabular top="minor" bottom="minor" left="minor" right="minor" width="120">
    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell><m>$a x</m></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell><m>$c x</m></cell>
      <cell><m>+</m></cell>
      <cell><m>$d</m></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell><m>$b</m></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>
    </li>
  </ol>

</aside>

<sideBySide widths="50% 50%">

  <div>
  <p><alert>Across</alert></p>
  <p>2. Is a factor of $q2</p>
  <p>3. Is a factor of $q4</p>
  <p>4. Is a factor of $q6</p>
  <p>5. Is a factor of $q8</p>

  <p><alert>Down</alert></p>
  <p>1. Is a factor of $q1</p>
  <p>2. Is a factor of $q3</p>
  <p>3. Is a factor of $q5</p>
  <p>4. Is a factor of $q7</p>
  </div>

  <div>
  <tabular top="minor" bottom="minor" left="minor" right="minor" width="360">
  
    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell>1<mathInput name="entry16" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell>2<mathInput name="entry24" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry25" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry26" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
    </row>
    
    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell>3<mathInput name="entry33" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry34" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry35" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell>4<mathInput name="entry42" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry43" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry44" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell>5<mathInput name="entry51" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry52" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry53" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>

    <row>
      <cell></cell>
      <cell><m>~~</m><mathInput name="entry62" minWidth="35"></mathInput></cell>
      <cell></cell>
